This paper deals with analyzing biological networks using graph theory and data structures. The focus is on comparing directed networks using directed graphlets, which suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a data structure called g-trie, which is commonly used in the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the computational demands of enumerating all graphlets in a large network, which could place it in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with biological networks, which could place it in the sub-category of Computational Biology and Bioinformatics (cs.CE).
